name: Will Miles
bio: Will Miles is a New York stand up comedian. After focusing on improvisation for two years at Chicago's ImprovOlympic, he began stand up comedy in 2007, and has been steadily working since he began. After performing in the local stand up scene for a couple of years in Chicago, his first work came in the opportunity to feature for Hannibal Buress on his "My Name Is Hannibal" Tour. He is a regular at clubs, working the Midwest and East Coast. Aside from his stand up, Miles won runner up in Break.com's national "Better Way Video" contest and is a regular contributor on Chicago Public Radio's "The Morning Amp" radio show hosted by Brian Babylon and Molly Adams.
